pageContext.claim: “But now, you have more caravans forming and they're on their way up, thousands and thousands of people. We don't know where they're from, who they are, nothing. We need strong borders. We need strong barriers and walls. Nothing else is going to work.”
pageContext.analysis: News reports the new caravan had about 500 people. These are people seeking asylum in the United States so a wall would not stop them from seeking entry at the border for possible processing.
